glosses.gloss: An engine that provided medieval artillery used during sieges; a heavy war engine for hurling large stones and other missiles
The ballista, plural ballistae, sometimes called bolt thrower, was an ancient missile weapon that launched a large projectile at a distant target.
A catapult is a ballistic device used to launch a projectile a great distance without the aid of explosive devices—particularly various types of ancient and medieval siege engines.
A trebuchet is a catapult, a common type of siege engine which uses a swinging arm to throw a projectile.
The arbalest was a late variation of the crossbow coming into use in Europe during the 12th century.
A mangonel was a type of catapult or siege engine used in the medieval period to throw projectiles at a castle's walls.
Type of catapult or siege engine used in the medieval period
An ancient military engine, in the form of a crossbow, used for hurling large missiles.
A military engine formerly used for throwing stones and burning objects.
A medieval siege engine consisting of a large pivoting arm heavily weighted on one end. Considered to be the technological successor to the catapult.
발리스타란 고대 로마 시대의 사출 병기로, 멀리 떨어진 목표물에게 커다란 발사체를 쏘아보냈다.
투석기는 돌을 던져 공격하는 공성병기로, 대포가 개발된 이후 현재는 쓰이지 않는 옛날의 무기이다.
트레뷰셋은 중세에 발명된 공성병기로, 투석기의 일종이다.
